    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Radiant Baldachin's Blessing</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img title="radiant_baldachins_blessing_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/radiant_baldachins_blessing_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="radiant baldachins blessing elden ring wiki guide 200px" width="200" height="200"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="width: 175px;"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft">
        Uses FP to temporarily raise poise 
      </div> </td> 
     <td><img title="attribute-scaling-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18" src="/file/Elden-Ring/attribute-scaling-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="attribute scaling elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">Scaling 
      <div class="lineleft">
        - 
       <br> 
       <br> 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>FP Cost</td> 
     <td>20</td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Radiant Baldachin's Blessing</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables">Consumable Item</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. Most <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>&nbsp;grant various effects such as restorative properties for recovering HP, removing certain negative status effects or applying temporary buffs and debuffs, while others can be thrown at enemies to deal damage.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Protection of a hidden temple in the guise of a bedchamber. This blessing is of the utmost rarity.<br></em></p> 
 <p><em>Uses FP to temporarily raise poise. <br>The effect lasts longer than a mere favor.<br></em></p> 
 <p><em>It's said a deathbed companion will only produce a blessing of this kind for a champion but once in her entire life. The sole blessing which she imbues of her own volition. </em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Radiant Baldachin's Blessing Use in Elden Ring:</h3> 
<p><strong>Radiant Baldachin's Blessing</strong> has the following effects:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Costs 20 FP to use</li> 
 <li>When used, grants&nbsp;+35% physical damage negation and +81% poise for 70 seconds</li> 
 <li>Also prevents stagger from attacks with damage level 0, 1, and 8 for 70 seconds</li> 
</ul> 
<p>This is a&nbsp;<strong>Body&nbsp;</strong><strong>Buff</strong>&nbsp;and will not&nbsp;stack with other buffs of the same type.</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>See&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Buffs and Debuffs" href="/Buffs+and+Debuffs" target="">Buffs and Debuffs</a>&nbsp;for more information on stacking buffs.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Radiant Baldachin's Blessing in Elden Ring</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Received from&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Fia" href="/Fia">Fia</a> after giving her the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Cursemark of Death" href="/Cursemark+of+Death">Cursemark of Death</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Deeproot Depths" href="/Deeproot+Depths" target="">Deeproot Depths</a> after defeating <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Fia's Champions" href="/Fia's+Champions" target="">Fia's Champions</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Radiant Baldachin's Blessing use in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p><strong>Radiant Baldachin's Blessing</strong>&nbsp;uses FP to temporarily raise physical absorption (35% without any armor applied). Note that it is a one-time use consumable.</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Radiant Baldachin's Blessing Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Only one can be obtained per each playthrough.</li> 
 <li>It is a one-time-consumable item like the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Baldachin's Blessing" href="/Baldachin's+Blessing">Baldachin's Blessing</a>.</li> 
 <li>Unlike <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Baldachin's Blessing" href="/Baldachin's+Blessing">Baldachin's Blessing</a>, It does <em>not</em> reduce Max HP from holding it in the inventory, so the player can safely keep it.</li> 
 <li>You can store Radiant Baldachin's Blessing.</li> 
 <li>Does carry over into NG+.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
